Colour in preservative: Dorsum yellowish brown, scattered with distinct, dark­brown spots of diameter about ¼–¾ that of eye, some of them coalesced to form larger blotches (see
Fig. 1
). Spots extend on to the head, femur, inguinal zone, tibia, tarsus (absent on hands and feet) and sides to the mid­lateral fold. Upper lip yellow. Posterior part of thigh yellow to ashy brown with dark­brown spots. Venter a uniform dull yellow, slightly lighter than background colour of dorsum.
